 The 
\emph on
total
\emph default
 rent was just that, the 
\emph on
return to landed property
\emph default
.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 So while land rent is not necessarily the exchange value 
\emph on
of
\emph default
 land, strictly speaking with 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

exchange value
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 meaning the socially necessary labor to produce it, land-rent is nonetheless
 the exchange value 
\emph on
appropriated
\emph default
 by virtue of the power vested through land ownership.
\end_layout

