\end_inset

.
\begin_inset Foot
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Haila's excellent review article is a landmark in the history of research
 on land rent.
 Nonetheless, it has some serious issues.
 One is its use of empiricist meta-theoretical categories, such as nomothetic
 generalization 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "willer1973systematic"

\end_inset

, to (mis)characterize conceptualization at different levels of abstraction,
 as is common in realist, particularly Marxist, social science (see below).
 This is compounded by characterizing 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

ideographic
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 research as 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

historical
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

nomothetic
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 as a search for general – and therefore implicitly ahistorical – laws.
 Instead, abstractions in critical-realist social research in general, and
 Marxist research in particular, generally are historical, and comprehension
 of even the most specific, concrete situation generally requires high-level
 abstractions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Another issue is the opposition between 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

accumulation
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

coordination,
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 which 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
after "276"
key "haila1990thetheory"

\end_inset

 subsumes under 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

the economic role of rent.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 But these are dialectical aspects of a single system rather than opposites.
 The pace, nature, and geography of accumulation depend on how the system
 is coordinated, and the structure of the system, how it regulates itself
 or not, the role of institutions – in other words, the character of its
 overall means of coordination – is vital to the process of accumulation.
 Indeed, this is the point of the present essay.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Furthermore, the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

economic
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 role of land rent is not limited to accumulation and coordination.
 It plays important roles in production, distribution, consumption, reproduction
, 
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

